     1→# Data Model: Email Processing Architecture Modernization
     2→
     3→**Feature**: 001-n8n-to-direct-migration
     4→**Date**: 2025-09-27
     5→**Status**: Complete
     6→
     7→## Entity Overview
     8→
     9→This data model preserves the sophisticated classification audit trail while optimizing for the new direct implementation architecture.
    10→
    11→## Core Entities
    12→
    13→### EmailMessage
    14→
    15→Primary entity representing a Gmail message with processing metadata, structured to match Gmail API payload.
    16→
    17→```typescript
    18→interface EmailMessage {
    19→  id: string; // Gmail message ID
    20→  threadId: string; // Gmail thread ID
    21→  gmailLabels: string[]; // Original Gmail labels (labelIds from Gmail API)
    22→
    23→  // Gmail API payload structure
    24→  payload: {
    25→    partId?: string;
    26→    mimeType: string;
    27→    filename?: string;
    28→    headers: EmailHeader[];
    29→    body?: MessagePartBody;
    30→    parts?: MessagePart[]; // For multipart messages
    31→  };
    32→
    33→  // Extracted/parsed fields for easier access
    34→  subject: string; // Extracted from headers
    35→  from: EmailAddress; // Parsed from "From" header
    36→  to: EmailAddress[]; // Parsed from "To" header
    37→  cc?: EmailAddress[]; // Parsed from "Cc" header
    38→  bcc?: EmailAddress[]; // Parsed from "Bcc" header
    39→  replyTo?: EmailAddress[]; // Parsed from "Reply-To" header
    40→  date: Date; // Parsed from "Date" header
    41→  messageId?: string; // Parsed from "Message-ID" header
    42→  inReplyTo?: string; // Parsed from "In-Reply-To" header
    43→  references?: string[]; // Parsed from "References" header
    44→
    45→  // Content (extracted from payload)
    46→  bodyPlain?: string;
    47→  bodyHtml?: string;
    48→  attachments?: EmailAttachment[];
    49→
    50→  // Gmail API metadata
    51→  snippet?: string; // Gmail-generated snippet
    52→  historyId?: string;
    53→  sizeEstimate?: number;
    54→
    55→  // Processing metadata
    56→  processedAt?: Date;
    57→  processingSessionId?: string;
    58→  isProcessed: boolean;
    59→
    60→  // Enhanced for parallel processing
    61→  processingBatch?: string; // Batch identifier for parallel processing
    62→  processingPriority: number; // Processing order within batch
    63→}
    64→
    65→interface EmailHeader {
    66→  name: string; // Header name (e.g., "From", "To", "Subject")
    67→  value: string; // Raw header value
    68→}
    69→
    70→interface EmailAddress {
    71→  email: string; // The actual email address
    72→  name?: string; // Display name (if provided)
    73→  raw: string; // Original header value for debugging
    74→}
    75→
    76→interface MessagePartBody {
    77→  attachmentId?: string;
    78→  size?: number;
    79→  data?: string; // Base64url encoded content
    80→}
    81→
    82→interface MessagePart {
    83→  partId: string;
    84→  mimeType: string;
    85→  filename?: string;
    86→  headers: EmailHeader[];
    87→  body?: MessagePartBody;
    88→  parts?: MessagePart[]; // Nested parts for complex structures
    89→}
    90→
    91→interface EmailAttachment {
    92→  attachmentId: string;
    93→  filename: string;
    94→  mimeType: string;
    95→  size: number;
    96→  isInline: boolean;
    97→  contentId?: string; // For inline attachments
    98→}
    99→```
   100→
   101→**Validation Rules**:
   102→
   103→- `id` must be valid Gmail message ID format (16-character alphanumeric string)
   104→- `threadId` must be valid Gmail thread ID format
   105→- `date` must be valid RFC 2822 timestamp
   106→- `from.email` must be valid RFC 5322 email address format
   107→- `to`, `cc`, `bcc` arrays must contain valid EmailAddress objects
   108→- `headers` must include required headers: "From", "Date", "Message-ID"
   109→- `payload.mimeType` must be valid MIME type (e.g., "text/plain", "text/html", "multipart/mixed")
   110→- `processingPriority` range: 1-100 (higher = more urgent)
   111→- `EmailAddress.email` must match RFC 5322 email format
   112→- `EmailAddress.raw` must preserve original header formatting for debugging
   113→
   114→**State Transitions**:
   115→
   116→```
   117→Unprocessed → Processing → Processed
   118→     ↓           ↓           ↓
   119→  Fetched → Classifying → Classified
   120→```
   121→
   122→### ClassificationSession
   123→
   124→Represents a batch classification session with enhanced audit capabilities.
   125→
   126→```typescript
   127→interface ClassificationSession {
   128→  id: string; // UUID
   129→  startedAt: Date;
   130→  completedAt?: Date;
   131→  emailCount: number;
   132→  successCount: number;
   133→  errorCount: number;
   134→
   135→  // Enhanced for new architecture
   136→  processingMode: 'parallel' | 'sequential';
   137→  batchSize: number;
   138→  performanceMetrics: {
   139→    totalDurationMs: number;
   140→    avgEmailDurationMs: number;
   141→    parallelStagesCount: number;
   142→    databaseBatchOps: number;
   143→  };
   144→
   145→  // Configuration snapshot
   146→  configVersion: string; // Hash of configuration used
   147→  configSnapshot: object; // Full config for reproducibility
   148→
   149→  // Error tracking
   150→  errors: ClassificationError[];
   151→  warnings: ClassificationWarning[];
   152→}
   153→```
   154→
   155→**Validation Rules**:
   156→
   157→- `successCount + errorCount` must equal `emailCount`
   158→- `completedAt` must be after `startedAt`
   159→- `configVersion` must match current config hash
   160→
   161→### EmailClassification
   162→
   163→Core classification result with preserved sophistication and enhanced explainability.
   164→
   165→```typescript
   166→interface EmailClassification {
   167→  id: string; // UUID
   168→  emailId: string; // Foreign key to EmailMessage
   169→  sessionId: string; // Foreign key to ClassificationSession
   170→
   171→  // Classification results
   172→  primaryCategory: string;
   173→  secondaryCategories: string[];
   174→  confidence: number; // 0.0 - 1.0
   175→
   176→  // Enhanced explainability
   177→  explainabilityTrace: ExplainabilityTrace;
   178→  scoreBreakdown: ScoreBreakdown;
   179→  attributeContext: AttributeContext;
   180→
   181→  // Processing metadata
   182→  processedAt: Date;
   183→  processingDurationMs: number;
   184→  aiRoutingUsed: boolean;
   185→
   186→  // Parallel processing context
   187→  batchPosition: number;
   188→  parallelStageResults: ParallelStageResult[];
   189→}
   190→```
   191→
   192→### ExplainabilityTrace (Enhanced)
   193→
   194→Detailed audit trail preserving all sophisticated classification reasoning.
   195→
   196→```typescript
   197→interface ExplainabilityTrace {
   198→  sessionId: string;
   199→  emailId: string;
   200→
   201→  // Pipeline stage results (preserved from n8n)
   202→  hardAssertions: HardAssertionResult[];
   203→  strongIndicators: StrongIndicatorResult[];
   204→  ruleScoring: RuleEvaluationResult[];
   205→  attributeDetection: AttributeDetectionResult[];
   206→  attributeInfluence: AttributeInfluenceResult[];
   207→  disambiguation: DisambiguationResult[];
   208→  multiLabelSelection: MultiLabelResult[];
   209→  aiRouting?: AIRoutingResult;
   210→
   211→  // Enhanced for debugging
   212→  stageTimings: Record<string, number>; // Stage execution times
   213→  parallelExecutionMap: Record<string, string[]>; // Which stages ran in parallel
   214→  configurationRefs: Record<string, string>; // Config sections used
   215→
   216→  // Decision audit
   217→  finalDecisionReason: string;
   218→  alternativeCategories: Array<{
   219→    category: string;
   220→    score: number;
   221→    eliminationReason: string;
   222→  }>;
   223→}
   224→```
   225→
   226→### ScoreBreakdown (Enhanced)
   227→
   228→Detailed score calculation with parallel processing context.
   229→
   230→```typescript
   231→interface ScoreBreakdown {
   232→  emailId: string;
   233→
   234→  // Category scores (preserved structure)
   235→  categoryScores: Record<
   236→    string,
   237→    {
   238→      baseScore: number;
   239→      hardAssertionBonus: number;
   240→      strongIndicatorScore: number;
   241→      ruleScore: number;
   242→      attributeInfluenceScore: number;
   243→      finalScore: number;
   244→
   245→      // Enhanced breakdown
   246→      parallelComputedComponents: string[]; // Which parts computed in parallel
   247→      computationDurationMs: number;
   248→      cacheHits: string[]; // Which calculations used cached results
   249→    }
   250→  >;
   251→
   252→  // Stage contributions
   253→  stageContributions: Record<
   254→    string,
   255→    {
   256→      contribution: number;
   257→      confidence: number;
   258→      processingMode: 'parallel' | 'sequential';
   259→      dependencies: string[]; // Other stages this depended on
   260→    }
   261→  >;
   262→
   263→  // Disambiguation tracking
   264→  disambiguationApplied: Array<{
   265→    categories: string[];
   266→    rule: string;
   267→    scoreAdjustment: number;
   268→    reason: string;
   269→  }>;
   270→}
   271→```
   272→
   273→### AttributeContext (Enhanced)
   274→
   275→Cross-cutting email attributes with parallel detection capabilities.
   276→
   277→```typescript
   278→interface AttributeContext {
   279→  emailId: string;
   280→
   281→  // Detected attributes (preserved)
   282→  urgency: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';
   283→  domains: string[];
   284→  structuralPatterns: string[];
   285→  temporalSignals: string[];
   286→
   287→  // Enhanced attribute detection
   288→  detectionMetadata: Record<
   289→    string,
   290→    {
   291→      detectedAt: Date;
   292→      confidence: number;
   293→      detectionMethod: 'rule' | 'pattern' | 'ai' | 'domain_lookup';
   294→      parallelProcessed: boolean;
   295→      dependencies: string[]; // Other attributes this detection depended on
   296→    }
   297→  >;
   298→
   299→  // Attribute influence tracking
   300→  influenceApplications: Array<{
   301→    targetCategory: string;
   302→    attributeUsed: string;
   303→    roleType: 'CORE' | 'PRIMARY_BOOST' | 'SECONDARY_BOOST' | 'DISAMBIGUATOR' | 'FILTER';
   304→    scoreImpact: number;
   305→    applicationReason: string;
   306→  }>;
   307→}
   308→```
   309→
   310→### Configuration Entities
   311→
   312→Enhanced configuration management supporting the sophisticated 9-stage classification pipeline.
   313→
   314→```typescript
   315→interface CategoryConfiguration {
   316→  version: string; // Semantic version
   317→  lastModified: Date;
   318→  hash: string; // Content hash for validation
   319→
   320→  // Main processing configuration
   321→  processing_config: ProcessingConfig;
   322→
   323→  // Validation metadata
   324→  schemaVersion: string;
   325→  validationPassed: boolean;
   326→  validationErrors: string[];
   327→
   328→  // Runtime optimization
   329→  compiledRules: CompiledRule[]; // Pre-compiled for performance
   330→  attributeMatrix: AttributeInfluenceMatrix; // Pre-computed influence matrix
   331→}
   332→
   333→interface ProcessingConfig {
   334→  version: number;
   335→  taxonomy_notes: string;
   336→  settings: ProcessingSettings;
   337→  category_signals: Record<string, CategorySignals>;
   338→  confidence_thresholds: ConfidenceThresholds;
   339→  multi_label_policy: MultiLabelPolicy;
   340→  domain_signal_overrides: DomainOverrides;
   341→  domain_signal_resolution: DomainResolution;
   342→  top_level_categories: Record<string, TopLevelCategory>;
   343→  attributes: AttributeSystem;
   344→  attribute_relevance: AttributeRelevanceMatrix;
   345→  ai_prompts: AIPromptSystem;
   346→  feature_extraction_schema: JSONSchema;
   347→}
   348→
   349→interface ProcessingSettings {
   350→  initialization: {
   351→    apply_hard_assertions: boolean;
   352→    seed_category_scores: boolean;
